Fidelity Brokerage Group chief to retire . Fidelity Investments said Sherif Nada , head of the institutional brokerage unit Fidelity Brokerage Group ( FBG ) , will retire on August 1 . Succeeding Nada , 55 , will be Kenneth Rathgeber , 49 , who is currently acting president of Fidelity Brokerage Services , the United Kingdom - based brokerage unit that is part of FBG . Rathberger will also succeed Nada on Fidelity ' s operating committee . Nada will continue as a senior vice president of Fidelity ' s parent company , FMR Corp , in a strategic role reporting to Gary Burkhead , vice chairman of FMR Corp and chief executive officer of Fidelity Institutional Group . 
